The paper focuses on modeling the perceived quality estimation in streaming services and real-time communications using multimedia frameworks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning (cs.AI), RTCP statistics (cs.IT), and video streaming (cs.CV), which further supports the inclusion of these sub-categories.
